WEBVTT

00:03.522 --> 00:07.327
Each year, Gospel and Life offers a daily devotional during the season of Lent.

00:07.687 --> 00:10.210
The 40 days from Ash Wednesday through Good Friday.

00:10.671 --> 00:15.998
You can sign up to receive these daily devotionals by email at gospelandlife.com slash lint.

00:16.018 --> 00:18.341
That's gospelandlife.com slash lint.

00:18.761 --> 00:20.964
Now here's Dr. Keller with today's teaching.

00:28.073 --> 00:32.338
We're going through the Book of First Peter in the evening, sermons in the evening, teaching,

00:33.314 --> 00:33.855
this year.

00:33.915 --> 00:42.588
And the section we're going to be looking at for several weeks is this section here, verses 13 to 21 of the first chapter.

00:42.628 --> 00:46.093
Tonight, however, we're only going to do an overview.

00:46.354 --> 00:54.746
It's a major section and it has a great deal to do with holiness, the holiness of God and our own holiness, our own personal holiness.

00:55.507 --> 00:57.330
And tonight, because we're

00:57.634 --> 00:59.097
We're going to be celebrating the Lord's Supper.

00:59.137 --> 01:02.042
What I'm going to do is say some things in a preliminary way.

01:02.122 --> 01:13.262
Lay out some real basics, just very, very broad basics, and do so in such a way that prepares us to come to the Lord's table tonight.

01:14.644 --> 01:19.252
Now the section that's printed is from verse 13 to 21, and it is a whole section.

01:19.473 --> 01:22.578
It is of a piece.

01:22.946 --> 01:29.612
But tonight, especially because we're really going to just talk about preliminaries, I'm only going to read from verse 13 through 16.

01:31.074 --> 01:31.534
Let's read.

01:32.775 --> 01:35.918
Therefore, prepare your minds for action.

01:37.080 --> 01:38.221
Be self-controlled.

01:39.021 --> 01:43.085
Set your hope fully on the grace to be given you when Jesus Christ is revealed.

01:44.066 --> 01:49.171
As obedient children, do not conform to the evil desires you had when you lived in ignorance.

01:49.832 --> 01:52.274
But just as he who called you is holy,

01:52.738 --> 02:01.947
So be holy in all you do, for it is written, be holy because I am holy."

02:03.648 --> 02:04.549
This is God's word.

02:06.311 --> 02:22.386
Let's not forget that first Peter is about how we can live in such a way that troubles and pain and suffering that inevitably come into our lives would not crush us or make us weaker things, but make us stronger

02:22.498 --> 02:26.265
refine our character, turn us into great people.

02:26.766 --> 02:28.169
How can you live in such a way?

02:28.229 --> 02:42.977
How can you be in such a condition that the troubles and the pains and the sufferings of life actually are tools that hone you and polish you and refine you?

02:43.017 --> 02:45.522
Everybody knows.

02:46.402 --> 02:52.350
For example, when a doctor comes in and says, no, I'm going to do this incision right here in your forehead.

02:52.370 --> 02:54.934
I'm going to get this little tumor out.

02:54.954 --> 02:56.476
I'm going to get this little scar out.

02:56.496 --> 02:57.517
I'm going to change things.

02:57.537 --> 03:03.505
I'm going to get this piece of metal out that was there as a resolving accident.

03:05.368 --> 03:07.291
The doctor comes in and is doing this incision.

03:07.411 --> 03:09.854
The one thing you don't do is, where are you going?

03:09.874 --> 03:10.996
You don't change.

03:11.056 --> 03:11.657
You don't move.

03:12.318 --> 03:15.602
Unless you're in the right condition, the very same stroke

03:15.778 --> 03:21.506
the very same hand, the very same blade, can kill you instead of heal you.

03:22.647 --> 03:29.556
And it depends, not completely on the skill of the hand, of the surgeon's hand, but it depends on whether you stay put.

03:30.217 --> 03:32.981
It depends on your position, it depends on your condition.

03:33.922 --> 03:36.245
And that's what the whole book of 1 Peter's about.

03:36.686 --> 03:37.928
How can you be the kind of person?

03:37.968 --> 03:45.618
How can you live in such a condition so that the surgical tools of the troubles and trials of life

03:45.730 --> 03:48.413
don't kill you, but instead actually heal you.

03:49.894 --> 03:54.518
Now, we've been looking to the first 12 verses of various things that Peter's been saying about this.

03:54.939 --> 03:57.341
And now in verse 13, there's a new section.

03:58.042 --> 04:10.593
The purpose of the new section is to really begin in earnest to tell us what it means to be the kind of people that will experience this refinement and this healing.

04:11.614 --> 04:15.698
And the basic point of this passage is you've got to be holy.

04:16.450 --> 04:21.457
What does it mean to sit still on the surgical bed of life?

04:21.658 --> 04:30.331
What does it mean to sit still under the blade of the troubles of life so that you're actually helped and refined by them instead of destroyed?

04:30.351 --> 04:32.073
You have to be holy.

04:34.377 --> 04:45.874
In fact, verse 13 tells us, therefore, since you want to be the kind of people who can rejoice in your tribulations, therefore prepare your minds for action.

04:46.050 --> 04:50.274
In the next couple of weeks, we're going to look at the various sections here, and we'll get back to this.

04:50.334 --> 04:56.840
But in the old authorized version, it says, gird up the loins of your mind.

04:56.880 --> 05:00.304
Now, that's literally what it says in Greek.

05:00.464 --> 05:01.805
It's what Peter actually wrote.

05:01.845 --> 05:04.688
Literally, it says, gird up the loins of your mind.

05:06.069 --> 05:06.850
You know what that means?

05:06.870 --> 05:08.872
It's a very picturesque statement.

05:08.912 --> 05:15.538
You know, of course, that the men and women of those days didn't wear what we wear today, but they wore flowing robes.

05:16.290 --> 05:19.995
And flowing robes were not conducive to strenuous action.

05:20.035 --> 05:24.020
They weren't good for running and for jumping and for climbing and for carrying.

05:24.481 --> 05:25.222
They got in the way.

05:25.583 --> 05:36.017
So when you wanted to prepare yourself for action, what you had to do is you had to pull together the flowing robes, all the flowing robes, and you had to put them into that which girded you, which was your belt.

05:36.277 --> 05:38.400
There'd always be a sash or a belt around you.

05:39.041 --> 05:40.303
That was what girded you.

05:40.343 --> 05:45.810
Well, you would pull up all of the flowing robes and stick them

05:45.890 --> 05:54.440
into the belt so that your bare legs were showing and you were ready to run if you had to, ready to jump, to climb, to carry.

05:54.640 --> 05:56.423
You were ready for strenuous action.

05:58.045 --> 06:07.616
So what Peter is trying to say is if you want to be the kind of people who can rejoice in tribulations and can grow during the troubles, you better get ready for some strenuous work.

06:08.157 --> 06:09.298
You better focus.

06:09.922 --> 06:14.829
See, the gird up the loins of your mind means, ah, you're distracted in every direction, are you not?

06:15.169 --> 06:16.651
You're thinking about a lot of things.

06:16.691 --> 06:17.873
You've got so many goals.

06:17.893 --> 06:19.215
You've got so many relationships.

06:19.675 --> 06:24.482
And so you give a little corner of your mind to seeking God.

06:25.122 --> 06:29.108
You give a little corner of your mind to the pursuit after God.

06:29.228 --> 06:32.813
No, Peter says, you've got to gird up the loins of your mind.

06:32.833 --> 06:33.814
You've got to get it all together.

06:33.834 --> 06:36.137
You've got to focus totally and get ready for action.

06:37.679 --> 06:39.602
This is not a hobby, seeking God.

06:39.938 --> 06:42.381
And not only that, he says, it's not just seeking God.

06:42.421 --> 06:47.768
What you need to be is right here in verse 16, be holy for I am holy.

06:47.868 --> 07:04.268
Now, what I want to do is just look at that phrase because that's the heart of the passage and lay out two principles, just to be holy for I am holy, be holy because I am holy.

07:04.588 --> 07:05.970
That teaches us two things.

07:07.010 --> 07:08.472
In a way, it teaches us three.

07:08.872 --> 07:10.294
Maybe we're my third one in there.

07:10.975 --> 07:12.718
First of all, it teaches us that God's holy.

07:14.019 --> 07:16.963
Secondly, it teaches us that we can be.

07:16.983 --> 07:18.706
In fact, we must be.

07:18.766 --> 07:20.388
It doesn't say you can be holy.

07:20.448 --> 07:21.870
It says you must be holy.

07:22.290 --> 07:23.031
Be holy.

07:24.153 --> 07:25.274
So first, God's holy.

07:25.375 --> 07:26.736
Secondly, we must be holy.

07:27.137 --> 07:28.959
And thirdly, I guess there is a third thing.

07:28.979 --> 07:32.444
And that is that we can be holy because God is holy.

07:32.845 --> 07:33.906
No hope otherwise.

07:34.178 --> 07:39.283
Let me just run through this and lay out some basic principles, all of which I will return to later.

07:40.244 --> 07:42.686
I mean, not later tonight, but later on in the series.

07:43.487 --> 07:46.790
First of all, the thing we see here, obviously, is God is holy.

07:46.870 --> 07:50.794
Let's just spend a few moments thinking about what that is.

07:52.395 --> 07:58.902
Peter quotes, be holy, for I am holy, and he quotes out of Leviticus.

07:59.302 --> 08:03.506
There's actually four or five places in the book of Leviticus where God says this.

08:03.842 --> 08:05.864
be holy, for I am holy.

08:06.444 --> 08:17.315
The word holy in the Old Testament is the Hebrew word kaddosh, which actually is one of those words that it almost sounds like what it means.

08:17.975 --> 08:27.524
What it actually means is to be separate, to be cut, cut, oh shh, to be cut off, to be cut loose.

08:28.826 --> 08:33.490
And what the word holiness really means is that God, if you want to

08:33.570 --> 08:37.595
Revere him as holy if you want to understand him as holy, if you want to see him as holy.

08:38.015 --> 08:42.321
You have to see him as infinitely above and beyond you and me.

08:44.083 --> 08:59.762
The Bible tells us that what makes him God is not that he's powerful, not that he's wise, not that he's loving, but that his power is holy power, his love is holy love, his wisdom is holy wisdom.

09:00.546 --> 09:05.674
And as soon as you put the word holy on God, what that means is God is off the scale.

09:07.918 --> 09:15.449
Whenever God wants to rebuke his people in the Old Testament, he very often says something like this, you thought I was one like yourself.

09:17.132 --> 09:19.075
For a couple moments, I want you to consider that.

09:19.516 --> 09:21.539
You might not think that's such a serious thing.

09:22.220 --> 09:24.424
Don't we have to think of God as like ourselves?

09:24.444 --> 09:25.645
And in a sense, we do.

09:25.726 --> 09:28.530
And God actually encourages it.

09:28.738 --> 09:32.986
Because he uses metaphors so we can understand him.

09:33.006 --> 09:36.031
He uses metaphors to describe himself that are similes.

09:36.552 --> 09:38.917
He says, I'm a father, so he's like the earthly father.

09:38.937 --> 09:40.519
He says, I'm a shepherd, like the shepherd.

09:41.281 --> 09:50.738
And yet what it means to honor him is holy is that we mustn't forget that inside all those metaphors God is infinitely above and beyond us so that what makes

09:50.946 --> 09:53.590
He is not at the top end of the scale of power.

09:53.871 --> 09:55.594
He's not the top end of the scale of love.

09:55.634 --> 09:57.677
He's not the top end of the scale of wisdom.

09:57.997 --> 10:01.383
But he is infinitely exalted above us, off the scale.

10:03.967 --> 10:04.748
Now, what does that mean?

10:05.970 --> 10:08.214
A couple of important, very important issues.

10:08.274 --> 10:10.738
What it means here is to honor him as holy.

10:10.850 --> 10:16.238
For example, all the places we're talking about him being holy talks about him being transcendently unique.

10:16.939 --> 10:19.603
First Samuel 220, there is none holy like the Lord.

10:20.164 --> 10:21.346
Or we sing it here.

10:21.807 --> 10:24.711
Exodus 15, 11, who is like unto thee?

10:26.434 --> 10:28.537
Now, by the way, that's my middle son's name.

10:28.777 --> 10:33.825
If you read it in Hebrew, when it says who is like unto thee, what are you saying is me, Ka'el, Michael.

10:34.085 --> 10:35.047
Anybody here named Michael?

10:35.548 --> 10:37.711
Do you know what that word, you know what Michael means in Hebrew?

10:38.312 --> 10:39.794
Me, Ka'el.

10:40.642 --> 10:44.067
Me who is like unto Elohim.

10:44.668 --> 10:46.310
Who is like unto God?

10:46.630 --> 10:47.532
That's what Michael means.

10:48.152 --> 10:49.314
It's a rhetorical question.

10:49.374 --> 10:51.017
The answer is nobody.

10:51.077 --> 10:52.078
Who is like unto thee?

10:52.118 --> 10:56.945
Oh Lord, among gods, who is like unto thee, glorious in holiness.

10:58.026 --> 11:01.131
So the word holiness means remember that he's not like you.

11:01.171 --> 11:02.953
Remember that he's transcendently unique.

11:02.973 --> 11:06.418
Remember that he's infinitely exalted above anything you can dare ask or think.

11:07.266 --> 11:08.307
Now, why should we do that?

11:08.347 --> 11:10.910
What happens if we think of him as like us?

11:11.091 --> 11:14.355
What happens if we fail to sanctify him as holy?

11:15.176 --> 11:16.457
No, the answers go like this.

11:17.078 --> 11:29.173
One of my wife and my wife, Kathy and my one of our favorite examples of this, which we use in a number of ways, you can illustrate a number of things, is the time when we only had one child and that first child was a baby and that first child was always sick.

11:29.733 --> 11:32.937
And Kathy was feeling tremendously worried, why is God doing this to us?

11:33.318 --> 11:36.722
And she sat rocking and looked up at a

11:36.834 --> 11:40.257
calligraphy that we still have up on the wall from Isaiah 55.

11:40.277 --> 11:47.785
There's a place in Isaiah 55 where it says, my thoughts are not your thoughts and my ways are not your ways.

11:48.986 --> 11:57.474
For as much as the heavens are higher than the earth, so my ways are above your ways and my thoughts above your thoughts.

11:58.795 --> 11:59.416
You know what he's saying?

11:59.796 --> 12:00.757
He's saying, I'm holy.

12:02.719 --> 12:04.421
He's saying, here you are worrying.

12:04.441 --> 12:05.682
You know why you're worrying?

12:06.018 --> 12:08.061
Oh man, you know why you're worrying, oh woman?

12:08.441 --> 12:11.164
Because you're thinking that I'm just at the top of the scale.

12:11.204 --> 12:13.687
You're comparing yourself to me.

12:13.748 --> 12:17.292
You're saying, you know, God isn't handling this very well.

12:17.893 --> 12:19.394
He's not running my life very well.

12:20.296 --> 12:21.297
I think I could run it better.

12:21.337 --> 12:24.761
But my ways are not your ways, my thoughts are not your thoughts.

12:25.662 --> 12:28.426
The reason you're worried is you are not sanctifying me as holy.

12:28.506 --> 12:30.148
My wisdom is holy wisdom.

12:32.090 --> 12:35.314
It's infinitely above any wisdom that you know of.

12:36.290 --> 12:42.996
You better start relaxing and you're not relaxing, says God, because you are not saying that my wisdom is holy wisdom.

12:43.477 --> 12:45.419
And it's above anything that you can imagine.

12:45.899 --> 12:48.421
Don't try to sit there and compare it to yours.

12:49.943 --> 12:57.109
Sanctify me as holy and actually as threatening as I say, 55 was on that day.

12:57.129 --> 13:06.258
It was tremendously comforting for Cathy to suddenly realize, oh my gosh, his ways are higher than my ways and his thoughts are higher than my thoughts.

13:06.466 --> 13:08.850
And therefore, I can sanctify him as holy.

13:08.890 --> 13:20.126
And what that means is you stop worrying, and the latter part of the passage says, therefore, you will be led forth in peace, and you will go out and joy.

13:20.146 --> 13:25.654
And the mountains will break forth before you into singing, and the trees will clap their hands.

13:26.155 --> 13:28.478
Just sanctify me as holy, and you'll be able to relax.

13:28.839 --> 13:29.981
Let me give you another example.

13:31.062 --> 13:36.370
Something people are constantly concerned about is they say, because I had a bad father,

13:36.546 --> 13:45.554
Because I've had bad experiences with fathers or with authority figures or with men, I just can't.

13:46.370 --> 13:51.236
comprehend or be comforted by all this Bible talk about God being a father.

13:51.276 --> 13:52.317
I just can't get into that.

13:52.357 --> 13:55.821
I never had a father that was good to me and I can't get into it at all.

13:56.142 --> 14:03.911
Now, I don't want to minimize that and I don't want anything, I don't want you to think that anything I say right now is making light of that or saying that's not a problem.

14:03.991 --> 14:06.354
Of course it's a problem, but here's the solution to the problem.

14:06.975 --> 14:09.398
He is what Jesus said he was.

14:09.978 --> 14:11.240
Watch Jesus when he prays.

14:11.320 --> 14:13.042
Go to John 17.

14:13.538 --> 14:18.264
You know, John 17 is the one place where we have a page out of Jesus Christ's quiet time notebook.

14:20.548 --> 14:22.270
A place where we can see how he prayed.

14:22.310 --> 14:25.414
And when he approached God, what did he call him?

14:26.456 --> 14:27.637
Holy Father.

14:28.318 --> 14:29.440
Holy Father.

14:29.480 --> 14:31.643
What is he saying?

14:31.703 --> 14:38.612
He's saying God is a father above any father that you could possibly know.

14:38.672 --> 14:40.735
His love is unending.

14:41.396 --> 14:42.738
His love is unconditional.

14:43.074 --> 14:44.196
His love is pure.

14:44.696 --> 14:45.858
His love is perfect.

14:46.599 --> 14:52.688
And ultimately, until you and unless you sanctify Him as holy, you're never going to understand that.

14:53.069 --> 14:55.052
You're never going to be comforted by His love.

14:55.993 --> 15:01.141
Now, people who are saying, well, I can't believe that God will love me because my father didn't love me unconditionally.

15:01.181 --> 15:01.482
All right.

15:01.802 --> 15:03.064
Sanctify God as holy.

15:03.084 --> 15:05.087
Take seriously that He's holy.

15:05.307 --> 15:06.790
Reflect on the fact that He's holy.

15:07.030 --> 15:08.993
Listen to what Jesus is about Him being holy.

15:10.996 --> 15:12.338
Are you going to believe Him or not?

15:13.378 --> 15:14.239
Why wouldn't you?

15:14.279 --> 15:23.213
And to believe in means that you don't have to be afraid of losing his father love, only wounding his father love, because he's a holy father.

15:23.233 --> 15:26.277
Do you see what it means to sanctify him as holy?

15:26.618 --> 15:29.903
His love is beyond anything we know, or dare ask or think.

15:30.243 --> 15:33.087
His wisdom is beyond anything we know, or dare ask or think.

15:33.388 --> 15:38.355
And therefore, there's a lot of talk in the Bible about abasing yourself before the holiness of God.

15:39.938 --> 15:41.320
You will never hit peace.

15:41.440 --> 15:42.802
You will never relax.

15:43.714 --> 15:53.524
until you start to realize that if he's really God, if he's really holy, that means that a certain point is I have to put my hand over my mouth.

15:53.564 --> 15:54.665
I've got to stop complaining.

15:54.685 --> 15:55.947
I've got to stop comparing him.

15:57.088 --> 16:00.471
And I've got to start receiving what he is and who he is and what he's done.

16:01.572 --> 16:07.338
Some years ago, I remember doing a new member interview and I asked a woman, when did you first become a Christian?

16:07.378 --> 16:10.201
And she said, well, I want to, let me ask you this.

16:10.241 --> 16:10.962
She said,

16:11.522 --> 16:12.825
There's two dates in my life.

16:12.845 --> 16:21.042
There was a date in which I really came to understand Christianity and I came to understand the teachings and I decided to believe in the teachings.

16:21.503 --> 16:27.034
But then later on there was a day when I realized if God was really who He said He was, it changes everything.

16:27.075 --> 16:30.642
If God is really who He said He is, if He says magnificent,

16:31.202 --> 16:36.490
As the Bible says, if he's everything that he says he is, I cannot trifle with him anymore.

16:36.610 --> 16:38.152
I can't play with him anymore.

16:38.573 --> 16:42.779
I can't sort of make him into a sort of a sugar daddy anymore.

16:43.040 --> 16:45.303
I can't go to him only when I'm in trouble anymore.

16:45.323 --> 16:47.446
It changes everything.

16:47.466 --> 16:49.810
Every part of my life has to come in underneath him.

16:51.192 --> 16:52.834
So I don't know which day I became a Christian.

16:52.854 --> 16:54.256
I said, let's try the second one.

16:55.418 --> 17:00.626
Because it was on that day that you experienced the holiness of God.

17:01.506 --> 17:04.290
That was the first time that you sanctified him.

17:04.430 --> 17:06.874
The word sanctified and the word holy is the same thing.

17:07.034 --> 17:08.116
You separated him.

17:08.176 --> 17:10.419
You saw him as above everything else.

17:10.639 --> 17:16.267
He was no longer another book on the shelf with all the other enrichment programs of your life.

17:17.029 --> 17:23.838
You ditched every other priority and you saw him as separate, unique.

17:24.620 --> 17:27.844
He wasn't like even just your first priority, then you had your second, your third, and your fourth.

17:28.105 --> 17:29.106
He was your first.

17:29.282 --> 17:32.265
priority, and your second priority, and your third priority.

17:34.427 --> 17:37.310
Why is there so much pain and suffering in the world?

17:37.791 --> 17:43.696
And how do we handle it in a way that won't destroy us, but could actually make us stronger, wiser, and more hopeful?

17:44.417 --> 17:53.867
All month long on Gospel and Life, Tim Keller is teaching from the book of 1 Peter, and looking at how Peter encouraged early believers who were facing intense suffering and pain.

17:54.587 --> 17:57.170
In his book, Walking with God Through Pain and Suffering,

17:57.218 --> 18:05.105
Dr. Keller takes a deeper look at how, with God's help, we can face life's most intense challenges and confront the hard questions on suffering.

18:05.645 --> 18:11.871
Through deep pastoral insight and real life stories, Dr. Keller explores how we can face pain and suffering in our own lives.

18:12.431 --> 18:21.939
This month, walking with God through pain and suffering is our thank you for your gift to help Gospel and Life share the message of Christ's love and compassion with people all over the world.

18:22.440 --> 18:27.204
So request your copy today at gospelandlife.com.

18:27.184 --> 18:32.009
Now here's Dr. Keller with the remainder of today's teaching.

18:35.132 --> 18:37.755
Who can stand before the Lord, O men of Beth Shemesh?

18:39.777 --> 18:40.839
Who is like unto thee?

18:40.919 --> 18:44.663
Sanctify the Lord for he alone is holy.

18:44.903 --> 18:45.884
That's what it means.

18:46.384 --> 18:53.392
To be holy means to see him as utterly separate, infinitely and transcendently unique, infinitely exalted above us.

18:54.073 --> 18:55.314
Do you see?

18:55.458 --> 19:01.826
But then the second point, and the second principle I want to lay down, is because he's holy, we must be holy.

19:01.946 --> 19:03.027
Well, now what does that mean?

19:03.648 --> 19:06.552
Does that mean we have to be transcendently unique?

19:06.572 --> 19:10.817
Does that mean that we have to somehow be infinitely exalted above all of creation?

19:11.277 --> 19:12.639
No, it can't mean that.

19:13.019 --> 19:13.941
So what does the word mean?

19:14.321 --> 19:20.188
Now it means something different, obviously, when applied to the creatures like us as opposed to the Creator.

19:20.569 --> 19:22.711
And yet the word still means separate.

19:23.172 --> 19:23.973
And here's what it means.

19:24.073 --> 19:24.914
In the Bible,

19:25.442 --> 19:29.988
There's a lot of inanimate objects that are made separate, that are made holy.

19:30.429 --> 19:33.313
There's a number of places where it says, your tithe is holy.

19:34.455 --> 19:40.122
When you give away 10% of your income to God in Leviticus 27, it says your tithe is their holy.

19:43.087 --> 19:49.215
It talks about linen being made holy, oil being made holy, pots being made holy.

19:50.116 --> 19:51.378
How could they become holy?

19:51.746 --> 20:06.923
The answer is, anything that was put into the temple of the tabernacle or anything that was put completely at God's disposal for the exclusive use of God, to be holy meant to be wholly devoted, to be totally devoted.

20:07.683 --> 20:09.906
You see, to be separated unto God.

20:09.926 --> 20:16.032
And you see, we're all holy to the degree that we are completely and totally devoted to Him.

20:16.673 --> 20:17.394
That's what it means.

20:17.474 --> 20:21.138
Now, to give you, there's a lot we can say about this.

20:21.890 --> 20:24.834
Holiness is such a comprehensive concept.

20:26.897 --> 20:33.566
And it's maybe the key ethical concept in understanding what it means to live a godly and light, a godly life.

20:33.606 --> 20:34.367
What does it mean to be holy?

20:34.387 --> 20:37.170
But let me just lay this one down and let me illustrate it.

20:37.611 --> 20:39.333
And this is the last thing we're going to do here tonight.

20:39.974 --> 20:40.955
I'm just going to illustrate it.

20:40.995 --> 20:45.662
To be holy means to be holy gods.

20:46.262 --> 20:48.946
It means no area of your life.

20:49.090 --> 20:50.031
doesn't belong to Him.

20:50.471 --> 20:54.176
It means no priority of your life is not judged by Him.

20:54.816 --> 20:58.360
It means no part of your heart does not belong to Him.

20:58.881 --> 21:00.122
It means to be totally devoted.

21:00.162 --> 21:01.864
That's why the tithe was holy.

21:01.884 --> 21:02.745
Why was the tithe holy?

21:02.945 --> 21:07.590
Because it was completely used for God's work, completely used for God's use.

21:07.970 --> 21:09.712
It was totally at God's disposal.

21:11.054 --> 21:12.856
Now none of us can be completely holy.

21:13.456 --> 21:15.378
None of us can be perfectly holy.

21:16.480 --> 21:18.642
However, this is what we're aiming at.

21:18.882 --> 21:20.445
And this is what we're called to be.

21:20.565 --> 21:23.510
And this is what, as we will see in the future, we can be.

21:25.553 --> 21:28.058
God would not call us to something that was an impossibility.

21:28.919 --> 21:30.221
So what does it mean to be totally devoted?

21:30.261 --> 21:44.626
Let me illustrate it from a very, very obscure and brief story from the Old Testament, which I think shows us perfectly what

21:44.802 --> 21:47.045
holiness is as total devotion.

21:47.465 --> 21:51.370
In 2 Samuel 23, verses 13 to 17, you can read it sometime.

21:51.410 --> 21:52.031
Don't read it now.

21:52.472 --> 21:53.273
It was very short.

21:54.414 --> 21:56.997
And it's so short that many people have never never seen it.

21:58.219 --> 21:58.900
This is what we're told.

21:59.140 --> 22:05.568
David, when he became king of Israel, his old enemies, the Philistines, rose up against him now.

22:05.608 --> 22:10.474
You know, as Jackie Mason used to call them, the uncircumscribed Philistines rose up against him.

22:12.116 --> 22:13.778
And because David was a new king,

22:14.850 --> 22:17.333
Some of you didn't get that, did you?

22:17.614 --> 22:20.357
I want you to go home and ask your friends what that meant.

22:20.417 --> 22:21.839
But it was really very funny.

22:23.541 --> 22:24.242
Just want you to know.

22:24.262 --> 22:29.709
The Philistines moved against David because they didn't want him to get consolidated.

22:29.729 --> 22:32.052
They didn't want him to become powerful.

22:32.493 --> 22:42.866
So as soon as he was made king over Israel, the Philistines drove into Judah and they tried to bisect

22:43.234 --> 22:43.995
Israel.

22:44.075 --> 22:53.890
They tried to capture David, and they came in so far that they took over the city of Bethlehem, which was David's home city, and they put a strong garrison of soldiers there.

22:55.572 --> 23:09.473
And then David was forced to flee into the wilderness of Judah out into the desert in a terrible place, and he was forced to set up his camp there and to stay on the run and to do his campaign of defense from that headquarters.

23:10.194 --> 23:12.978
And he got around him a number of what the Bible

23:13.154 --> 23:19.865
calls his mighty men, a number of strong and valiant and skillful warriors.

23:20.626 --> 23:28.039
Now one day, under the very, very hot desert sun, David just murmured a deep desire.

23:28.259 --> 23:37.394
The Bible tells us he was hot, he was discouraged, he was thinking, will I ever be able to

23:38.978 --> 23:40.641
will ever be able to resist the Philistines?

23:40.661 --> 23:43.125
Will the Lord deliver Israel back into my hands?

23:43.145 --> 23:45.288
Will the Lord deliver Bethlehem back into my hands?"

23:45.910 --> 23:51.359
And he was remembering his hometown, and he was under the hot sun, and he murmured a deep desire.

23:52.601 --> 24:01.495
Maybe he wasn't even talking to anybody, but we know he said, oh, that I could have a drink from the well by the gate of Bethlehem.

24:02.557 --> 24:03.058
That's all I said.

24:03.490 --> 24:06.654
Oh, that I might have a drink from the well by the gate of Bethlehem.

24:06.674 --> 24:07.995
That didn't mean he didn't have a well there.

24:08.015 --> 24:10.718
He had to have a well, or you wouldn't have been able to have a camp.

24:11.779 --> 24:15.303
However, that well was particularly tasty.

24:15.383 --> 24:18.186
The water there had sweet kinds of minerals in it.

24:18.727 --> 24:30.920
But most of all, he was yearning for the day in which he would have Bethlehem back, and he was anxious, and he was wrestling with the idea, will God really protect me?

24:31.361 --> 24:32.402
Will he honor me?

24:32.674 --> 24:34.376
Will he help me and aid me?"

24:34.957 --> 24:40.404
So he says, oh, that I would have the water, a drink of water from the well of Bethlehem.

24:41.185 --> 24:41.906
Now, what happened?

24:42.326 --> 24:43.988
He was not giving anybody a command.

24:44.829 --> 24:46.391
He was not asking for volunteers.

24:46.671 --> 24:48.093
He wasn't even talking to anybody.

24:48.334 --> 24:51.117
He was just sighing deeply and expressing a desire.

24:51.778 --> 24:53.300
What happened next is amazing.

24:54.021 --> 24:59.027
We're told that three of his mighty men, three of his warriors, overheard his wish.

25:00.429 --> 25:01.490
They looked at each other.

25:02.850 --> 25:03.691
They said nothing.

25:04.312 --> 25:10.000
They belted on their swords, they picked up a water pitcher, and they went off toward Bethlehem.

25:10.460 --> 25:15.587
And we're told, incredibly, that they fought their way into Bethlehem.

25:16.528 --> 25:21.014
They would have had to have fought their way up a hill, whose scores of Philistine soldiers there.

25:21.615 --> 25:27.383
They would have had to fight their way into the gate because we know the well by the gate of Bethlehem was inside the city.

25:28.785 --> 25:32.850
Two of them would have probably had to be fighting people off while one of them was filling the water jug.

25:33.602 --> 25:35.385
then they would have had to fight their way out.

25:36.206 --> 25:44.199
And worst of all, once they finally got out, which they did, they had to go through the desert carrying the water instead of drinking it.

25:46.082 --> 25:55.858
And finally, they came into the presence of their king, David, and they said, here's the water from the gate, the well at the gate of Bethlehem that you desired.

25:56.514 --> 26:04.502
and David was absolutely thunderstruck, and he looked at the water, and we're told this, and the Bible says, and he refused to drink it.

26:04.622 --> 26:11.188
Instead, he took it, and he poured it out on the ground before the Lord, saying, far be it from me, O Lord, to do this.

26:11.369 --> 26:17.214
Is it not the blood of the men who went at the risk of their lives?

26:19.136 --> 26:22.860
And the story concludes, and David would not drink of it.

26:24.161 --> 26:25.202
Now, what do we learn?

26:26.050 --> 26:27.611
about total devotion.

26:28.512 --> 26:30.194
What do we learn about holiness from this?

26:30.654 --> 26:32.156
We learn three things and here they are.

26:32.676 --> 26:35.799
Number one, first of all, we learn the nature of total devotion.

26:35.839 --> 26:36.640
Look here, look here.

26:36.680 --> 26:55.858
To be totally devoted to somebody, to be totally in love with them, to be totally separated onto them means that the difference between a command and a request and just a sigh is non-existent, no difference.

26:56.898 --> 26:57.980
A sigh is enough.

26:58.040 --> 27:03.267
If I'm totally devoted to somebody, devoted to my king, a sigh is all it takes.

27:04.169 --> 27:10.338
It doesn't matter whether I'm being sent out against an army, your wish is my command.

27:12.040 --> 27:17.208
You see, total devotion means that there's no difference when a command and a request and just a sigh.

27:18.069 --> 27:21.214
Now this morning we talked about it under another heading, but here it is again.

27:21.614 --> 27:24.178
When you know that you're totally devoted to somebody,

27:24.290 --> 27:28.634
The pleasure of giving them pleasure becomes greater than the pleasure of taking pleasure.

27:29.575 --> 27:33.799
And their very sighs become your glad compulsion.

27:34.800 --> 27:36.202
You want to know what delights them.

27:36.762 --> 27:45.771
And you see their desires and their delights as commands, glad commands, joyous commands, total devotion.

27:46.511 --> 27:50.696
You see why holiness to be wholly devoted to God goes way beyond rules.

27:50.796 --> 27:53.298
It goes way beyond keeping codes.

27:54.370 --> 27:59.596
It's a whole orientation of heart that goes way beyond God's commands and even way beyond God's requests.

28:00.216 --> 28:11.208
But it just, it just yearns and stretches out to see anything that God prefers and wants and that we consider binding on ourselves.

28:11.589 --> 28:19.818
You know, when somebody says, when somebody comes to me and says, I understand that the Bible says we have to give a certain portion of our income to God.

28:19.838 --> 28:21.359
Now, how much is it?

28:22.621 --> 28:23.922
How much do I have to give?

28:24.226 --> 28:25.648
that a tenth is that much?

28:25.928 --> 28:28.091
What do I have to do to stay in good with God?

28:28.152 --> 28:31.556
And don't you see that question shows it is not arisen from a holy heart.

28:32.998 --> 28:37.505
You never ask, how much do I have to do if you're totally devoted?

28:37.545 --> 28:40.008
You ask, how much can I do?

28:40.048 --> 28:43.093
What does he want?

28:43.553 --> 28:45.556
Not just what he commands, not just what he requests.

28:46.778 --> 28:48.280
What are the desires of his heart?

28:48.480 --> 28:49.842
See, it's the delights

28:50.626 --> 28:53.751
of the heart of the person you're totally devoted to that you're really after.

28:53.951 --> 28:55.994
Not, well, what do I have to do to stay on your good side?

28:56.194 --> 28:56.835
What are the commands?

28:57.476 --> 28:58.418
What's the job description?

28:58.438 --> 28:58.998
What are the duties?

28:59.659 --> 29:02.043
A holy person doesn't care about those things.

29:02.383 --> 29:03.385
That's just the beginning.

29:03.425 --> 29:10.856
To be totally devoted is to say, your size are my glad compulsions.

29:11.277 --> 29:15.523
That's the nature of a holy heart, the nature of total devotion.

29:15.703 --> 29:20.210
But secondly, we're also taught here the object of total devotion.

29:21.570 --> 29:24.914
On the one hand, David is absolutely right.

29:26.615 --> 29:27.897
Why did David pour out the water?

29:28.497 --> 29:33.062
I mean, did anybody say, those poor guys, they almost got killed.

29:33.363 --> 29:34.244
They went all that way.

29:34.264 --> 29:37.127
How do you think they felt when he poured out that water?

29:37.888 --> 29:38.548
They felt honored.

29:38.588 --> 29:39.389
You know what he was doing?

29:40.110 --> 29:47.698
What he was saying is, on the one hand, the men's attitude toward David is wonderful.

29:48.130 --> 29:49.993
Because that's how we should all be loving each other.

29:50.013 --> 29:51.775
The Bible says be devoted to each other.

29:51.815 --> 29:52.997
That's a command.

29:53.137 --> 29:54.639
And you know what it means to be devoted to each other?

29:54.659 --> 29:57.724
To be devoted means you don't negotiate.

29:58.224 --> 29:59.386
You don't have to twist arms.

29:59.927 --> 30:02.270
You love each other spontaneously.

30:02.310 --> 30:04.313
David was surprised.

30:05.254 --> 30:08.939
If you have brothers and sisters who love you and the Lord, they're surprising you.

30:08.960 --> 30:10.422
You shouldn't have to be twisting their arm.

30:10.862 --> 30:11.984
They're looking for what you need.

30:12.004 --> 30:13.266
They're listening to your size.

30:13.826 --> 30:16.370
And they're surprising you with their spontaneous devotion.

30:16.738 --> 30:19.122
And if you're upset, you say, you know, nobody's doing that to me.

30:19.162 --> 30:21.225
Well, maybe somebody's thinking that about you.

30:21.265 --> 30:27.815
We shouldn't be, listen, in the Christian community, we shouldn't be twisting each other's arms and negotiating.

30:28.196 --> 30:33.023
We shouldn't have to be broadcasting our knees.

30:34.005 --> 30:35.327
We should be all after each other.

30:35.367 --> 30:36.188
We should be watching.

30:36.228 --> 30:39.954
We should be listening, overhearing, waiting to hear each other's sigh.

30:40.290 --> 30:42.874
and then surprising each other with spontaneous love.

30:42.894 --> 30:43.675
That's the nature thing.

30:43.696 --> 30:44.938
So we're supposed to be devoted to each other.

30:45.138 --> 30:46.480
But David is right.

30:46.841 --> 30:54.253
He poured out this because he said, I do not have the right to this level of devotion.

30:55.575 --> 30:59.060
Far be it for me, he says, to drink this.

30:59.181 --> 31:01.885
Is this not the blood of the men who went at the risk of their lives?

31:02.226 --> 31:05.010
In other words, he says, it is not to any human king.

31:05.122 --> 31:10.210
It is not to any human being that we should bring the water of our spontaneous devotion.

31:10.590 --> 31:12.072
It's to David's greater son.

31:12.133 --> 31:15.137
When we see David in this story, we see his greater son.

31:15.197 --> 31:19.864
We see the real anointed prince, the anointed prince of the world, the anointed prince of the universe.

31:20.205 --> 31:26.594
And to him and to him alone, should you give the water of your spontaneous love?

31:27.215 --> 31:28.978
Don't you dare give it to anybody else.

31:30.786 --> 31:33.549
Don't you dare treat anybody else the way these men treated David.

31:33.569 --> 31:35.011
David knew he didn't have the right to it.

31:36.632 --> 31:51.308
Some of you have got your lives all screwed up because you are bringing the water of your devotion to a human being who doesn't have the theological smarts and doesn't have the godliness to pour it on the ground and say, I don't have a right to this.

31:51.328 --> 31:52.370
They're taking it from you.

31:53.291 --> 31:54.792
Give it to nobody but Jesus.

31:57.715 --> 32:00.178
The only object of

32:00.930 --> 32:07.478
total devotion, the only object to which we should be wholly separated, the only object of total devotion is Jesus.

32:08.399 --> 32:11.503
But lastly, we see the nature of this total devotion.

32:11.984 --> 32:13.626
We see the object of this total devotion.

32:13.666 --> 32:15.669
Lastly, I'm going to give you the reason for this total devotion.

32:16.329 --> 32:17.952
You want to know how we can become holy?

32:17.992 --> 32:19.073
Here's how we become holy.

32:19.834 --> 32:21.136
Just a word of it, and then we're done.

32:21.176 --> 32:24.280
Later on, we'll in the series we can develop it more.

32:24.320 --> 32:29.426
When you read this story, you don't just see Jesus Christ in David.

32:30.178 --> 32:34.923
You see, Jesus Christ and the mighty man, listen, he is our warrior king.

32:34.943 --> 32:39.947
He broke through enemy lines to bring us the water of life.

32:43.171 --> 32:44.392
He broke through enemy lines.

32:44.512 --> 32:45.613
He's the warrior king.

32:45.633 --> 32:47.455
He looks at us.

32:48.516 --> 32:54.021
And he says in the book of John chapter 17, for their sakes, I sanctify myself.

32:54.061 --> 32:54.942
Do you know what that means?

32:56.143 --> 32:57.725
He says, I am wholly focused.

32:57.785 --> 32:59.026
I am wholly devoted.

32:59.330 --> 33:00.692
to you and to me.

33:00.732 --> 33:02.996
He's the warrior king.

33:03.016 --> 33:10.429
He hears our sighs and he goes up the hill and he fights through enemy lines to bring us the water of life.

33:10.789 --> 33:20.786
But listen, listen, if David thought that this was so precious that he couldn't drink of it because the water came at the risk of his men's life,

33:21.442 --> 33:25.067
How much more precious should the cup that you're about to drink here be precious to you?

33:25.148 --> 33:27.151
Because it didn't come at the risk of Jesus' life.

33:27.551 --> 33:29.254
It came at the price of his life.

33:31.337 --> 33:34.902
You see, David pours it out and says, this is the blood of the men who risked their lives.

33:34.942 --> 33:35.263
All right.

33:35.784 --> 33:41.552
The water of eternal life that Jesus Christ fought through enemy lines for is the cup of the new covenant.

33:41.613 --> 33:42.294
It is his blood.

33:43.756 --> 33:48.202
And as our warrior Savior brings us the water of life, we're not going to feel worthy either.

33:48.563 --> 33:50.546
But don't you dare pour it out on the ground.

33:51.586 --> 33:57.051
He doesn't want you to, because he says, think about the price I paid.

33:57.071 --> 34:00.134
Think about how I fought up that hill.

34:00.194 --> 34:03.137
Think about the fact that I was pierced by many wounds.

34:05.059 --> 34:09.383
And if you think enough about my devotion to you, you will become wholly devoted to me.

34:10.685 --> 34:17.511
If you think as much about my holiness, my matchless love for you, it will turn you into something wonderful.

34:18.713 --> 34:19.213
Don't you see?

34:19.293 --> 34:20.114
It's possible.

34:20.738 --> 34:25.886
Be holy for I am holy for you.

34:27.769 --> 34:28.249
Let's pray.

34:28.269 --> 34:37.483
Now, Father, help us to see as we pick up the cup that this is the water of life that your son fought through enemy lines for.

34:37.884 --> 34:47.538
Help us to understand that because he's holy, infinitely exalted, his love is beyond anything we've ever seen, because he's holy for us.

34:48.770 --> 34:50.573
It's possible for us to be holy for Him.

34:50.954 --> 34:52.837
Make us holy even as you are holy.

34:52.917 --> 34:54.079
We ask it in Jesus' name.

34:54.539 --> 34:54.840
Amen.

34:55.621 --> 34:58.205
We'll be on anything we've ever seen because He's holy for us.

34:59.788 --> 35:01.511
It's possible for us to be holy for Him.

35:01.892 --> 35:03.795
Make us holy even as you are holy.

35:03.855 --> 35:05.017
We ask it in Jesus' name.

35:05.477 --> 35:05.778
Amen.

35:11.668 --> 35:15.634
Thanks for listening to today's teaching from Tim Keller here at Gospel in Life.

35:16.066 --> 35:22.094
For the 40 days from Ash Wednesday through Good Friday, Gospel and Life would like to email you a daily lint devotional.

35:22.535 --> 35:26.200
You can sign up to receive these daily emails at gospelandlife.com.

35:26.220 --> 35:28.723
That's gospelandlife.com.

35:28.964 --> 35:32.008
Today's sermon was recorded in 1993.

35:32.188 --> 35:42.322
The sermons and talks you hear on the Gospel and Life podcast were recorded between 1989 and 2017, while Dr. Keller was senior pastor at Redeemer Presbyterian Church.

